req; (same terraform code, app a and app b keliye, alag alag state file)
same module/template use hona h
appa and appb ke liye alag alag state files create
jenkins se App_name parameter ke through krna h, means dynamically
root main.tf ko env ke andar shift krnege, seprate root.tf for both env or appa and appb
seperate state file, smae bucket, different prefix

jenkins pipipeline me define krdenge env as a parameter, so jo bhi para select krenge vo build hoga,
app-a select kiya, toh app-a ka state file store hoga bucket me
jenkins simply - cd env/app-a -> terraform init -> terraform apply


module -> base template, only need config
root -> tells module the config
tfvars -> app a ke liye ye config

flow- jenkins(env select)->terraform check backend.tf(decide kis env ki state bnegi)-> tfvars read(vm_name = "app-a-vm")
->root variable fill hoga (var.vm_name = "app-a-vm") -> root module give to vm module (vm_name = var.vm_name) ->
vm module creates resources-> statefile me store hoga(app-a/terraform.tfstate)